                "section_visibility": "always",
                "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"z05-feature-shell\"><section class=\"z05-section z05-overview-section\"><div class=\"z05-wrap\"><div class=\"z05-overview-head\"><div><p class=\"z05-kicker\">Overview</p><h2>A compact hybrid for people who rotate music</h2></div><p>Some IEMs are tuned for one perfect demo track. Z05 AuAg is built for the way most of us listen: albums, playlists, dongles, DAPs, desk chains, and a mood that changes by the hour.</p></div><div class=\"z05-overview-main\"><article><span>01</span><h3>What it is</h3><p>A compact universal hybrid you can live with daily: easy to carry, easy to drive, and serious enough for focused listening.</p></article><article><span>02</span><h3>Why AuAg</h3><p>The gold/silver finish gives the launch pair a bit of ceremony without turning it into a display-only object.</p></article><article><span>03</span><h3>What you get</h3><p>A monitor, cable, 3.5mm, 4.4mm balanced, and Type-C terminations, a carry case, and LiquidMorph tips, all ready to go.</p></article></div><div class=\"z05-overview-summary\"><div><h3>For the listener who changes albums before they change gear</h3><p>Run it from a phone dongle on the way out, then plug into a balanced player or desktop chain at home. The point is simple: keep the Z05 character with fewer little compromises.</p></div><div class=\"z05-overview-specs\" aria-label=\"Z05 AuAg overview specifications\"><article><span>Fit</span><p>No custom mold needed with LiquidMorph tips for a seal you can repeat.</p></article><article><span>Driver platform</span><p>Dynamic-driver body with armature speed and air layered on top.</p></article><article><span>Source path</span><p>3.5mm, 4.4mm balanced, and Type-C terminations in the box.</p></article><article><span>Finish</span><p>Forged-carbon faceplates with Au/Ag foil; 3D-printed shells finished by hand with matching foil lacing.</p></article></div></div></div></section></div><style>.z05-overview-section{background:#f4f1ea;color:#111}.z05